        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 4:22PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Aberdeen, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Amory, Aberdeen, Smithville, New Salem, Hatley, Sipsey Fork, Becker,
Quincy, Turon, Splunge, Wise Gap, Athens, East Aberdeen, Bigbee,
Greenwood Springs, and Parham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
